<subSubSection id="C32B6553FF8D3A78BBD2FB686389BA1F" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8E36D8FF8D3A78BBD2FB686389BA1F" blockId="3.[151,1437,1203,2037]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8D3A78BBD2FB686149BBCA" bold="true" box="[151,273,1203,1228]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Vei n R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BA2DFB196128BBD6" box="[360,368,1218,1232]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BA3CFB1961D8BBD6" box="[377,384,1218,1232]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="3.0">3</number>
short and straight, joining C ~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B9A2FB686352BBCD" box="[743,778,1203,1227]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="0.2">0.2</number>
distance between end of R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BF05FB196410BBD6" box="[1088,1096,1218,1232]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
and R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BFD1FB1964C4BBD6" box="[1172,1180,1218,1232]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="4.0">4</number>
(
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8D3A78BFEDFB6864A5BBCD" box="[1192,1277,1203,1228]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[176,1401,193,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1402,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Hemerodromia breviradia sp. nov., holotype ♂. 9. habitus, lateral view; 10. wing; 11. terminalia, lateral view; 12. cercus, dorsal view; 13. subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 14. phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 15. hypandrium, epandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252070/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BF9BFB6864A5BBCD" box="[1246,1277,1203,1227]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
); cell bm+dm long, ending after at level of R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BAB4FB3361A1BBF0" box="[497,505,1256,1270]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
, ~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B950FB026260BBF4" box="[533,568,1241,1266]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="2.5">2.5</number>
X as long as cell br (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8D3A78B861FB02632FBBF4" box="[804,887,1241,1266]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[176,1401,193,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1402,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Hemerodromia breviradia sp. nov., holotype ♂. 9. habitus, lateral view; 10. wing; 11. terminalia, lateral view; 12. cercus, dorsal view; 13. subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 14. phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 15. hypandrium, epandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252070/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B81DFB01632FBBF4" box="[856,887,1242,1266]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
); cercus narrow with pointed apex (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8D3A78BE49FB0265D6BBF4" box="[1292,1422,1241,1266]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[176,1401,193,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1402,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Hemerodromia breviradia sp. nov., holotype ♂. 9. habitus, lateral view; 10. wing; 11. terminalia, lateral view; 12. cercus, dorsal view; 13. subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 14. phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 15. hypandrium, epandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252070/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Figs 11, 12</figureCitation>
); phallus sclerotized, extending just beyond the hypandrium apex (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8D3A78B835FADB639BBA1F" box="[880,963,1280,1305]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[176,1401,193,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1402,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Hemerodromia breviradia sp. nov., holotype ♂. 9. habitus, lateral view; 10. wing; 11. terminalia, lateral view; 12. cercus, dorsal view; 13. subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 14. phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 15. hypandrium, epandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252070/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B8E1FADA639BBA1F" box="[932,963,1281,1305]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32B6553FF8D3A7EBB82FAFF62F3BEAB" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="214" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8E36D8FF8D3A7EBB82FAFF62F3BEAB" blockId="3.[151,1437,1203,2037]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,794]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="214" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8D3A78BB82FAFF6109BA3B" bold="true" box="[199,337,1316,1341]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8D3A78BA1AFAFF61C4BA3B" bold="true" box="[351,412,1316,1341]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8D3A78BAEFFAFF61B7BA3B" box="[426,495,1316,1341]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[176,1401,193,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1402,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Hemerodromia breviradia sp. nov., holotype ♂. 9. habitus, lateral view; 10. wing; 11. terminalia, lateral view; 12. cercus, dorsal view; 13. subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 14. phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 15. hypandrium, epandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252070/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BA9BFAFE61B7BA3B" box="[478,495,1317,1341]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8D3A78B946FAFF621BBA3B" bold="true" box="[515,579,1316,1341]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Head</emphasis>
. Dark brown to black, antenna and mouthparts yellow with all setae whitish; ocellar triangle with 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BAC4FA9261D7BA67" box="[385,399,1353,1377]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of proclinate ocellar setae; anterior ocellus larger. Eyes iridescent black, very narrowly separated on face which bears fine reclinate setulae. Frons with 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B82CFAB663CBBA83" box="[873,915,1389,1413]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
setulae; 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B8BDFAB66479BA83" box="[1016,1057,1389,1413]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
pairs of vertical setae contiguous with uniseriate postocular setae; occiput bearing scattered fine hairs. Clypeus with rather dense short downwardly directed pile. Proboscis slightly curved with setae yellow. Antenna with scape and pedicel bearing distinct short dorsal setulae; postpedicel about 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B95CFA026262BAF7" box="[537,570,1497,1521]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.3">1.3</number>
X as long as wide, stylus ~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B8CDFA0263F3BAF7" box="[904,939,1497,1521]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="0.8">0.8</number>
X as long as postpedicel. 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8D3A78BF9FFA03656BBAF7" bold="true" box="[1242,1331,1496,1521]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8D3A78BE03FA0365D5BAF7" box="[1350,1421,1496,1521]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[176,1401,193,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1402,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Hemerodromia breviradia sp. nov., holotype ♂. 9. habitus, lateral view; 10. wing; 11. terminalia, lateral view; 12. cercus, dorsal view; 13. subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 14. phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 15. hypandrium, epandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252070/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BE38FA0265D5BAF7" box="[1405,1421,1497,1521]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Elongate, slightly arched ventrally; dorsum yellow; antepronotum with anterior margin almost straight; scutum with yellow setae, very small and fine except 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B9E5F9FA62F6B93F" box="[672,686,1569,1593]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
notopleural and 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B82AF9FA6325B93F" box="[879,893,1569,1593]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of scutellars. 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8D3A78BF15F9FB6425B93F" bold="true" box="[1104,1149,1568,1593]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Leg</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8D3A78BFCBF9FB648BB93F" box="[1166,1235,1568,1593]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[176,1401,193,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1402,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Hemerodromia breviradia sp. nov., holotype ♂. 9. habitus, lateral view; 10. wing; 11. terminalia, lateral view; 12. cercus, dorsal view; 13. subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 14. phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 15. hypandrium, epandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252070/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BF86F9FA648BB93F" box="[1219,1235,1569,1593]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Whitish yellow. C 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BBE8F99E60EFB95B" box="[173,183,1605,1629]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BB9DF99E60A2B95B" box="[216,250,1605,1629]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.3">1.3</number>
X longer than distance between C 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B9C1F99E62D6B95B" box="[644,654,1605,1629]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
and C2, 
<date id="FF8F1018FF8D3A78B9BCF99F6342B95B" box="[761,794,1604,1629]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">5X</date>
as long as wide with some pale dorsoapical setae. F 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BE3FF99E65DCB95B" box="[1402,1412,1605,1629]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BBD2F9B260E0B987" box="[151,184,1641,1665]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.1">1.1</number>
X as long as C 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BA3FF9B261DDB987" box="[378,389,1641,1665]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
, 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BADDF9B361E1B987" box="[408,441,1640,1665]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="3.5">3.5</number>
–4.0X as long as wide. Femoral formula 
<date id="FF8F1018FF8D3A78B8F5F9B36477B987" box="[944,1071,1640,1665]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="2013-07-15" valueMax="2013-07-16" valueMin="2013-07-15">
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B8F5F9B363E5B987" box="[944,957,1640,1665]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="7.0">7</number>
/ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B883F9B36453B987" box="[966,1035,1640,1665]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="15.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="15.0">15–16</number>
/ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BF50F9B36477B987" box="[1045,1071,1640,1665]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="13.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="13.0">13</number>
</date>
–14/ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BF26F9B364D5B987" box="[1123,1165,1640,1665]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7</number>
, basal spines stronger; denticles confined to distal 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BA8FF95661B7B9A3" box="[458,495,1677,1701]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="0.7">0.7</number>
, becoming closer together distally, black, 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B883F956638CB9A3" box="[966,980,1677,1701]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="2.0">2</number>
rows linear, without distal discontinuity. T 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BBE9F96A60EEB9CF" box="[172,182,1713,1737]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BB9DF96A60A3B9CF" box="[216,251,1713,1737]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="0.7">0.7</number>
X as long as F 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BAEEF96A61EEB9CF" box="[427,438,1713,1737]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
, evenly curved, ventral face shallowly concave; with 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BF61F96A646AB9CF" box="[1060,1074,1713,1737]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="2.0">2</number>
rows of 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BFD8F96B64BAB9CF" box="[1181,1250,1712,1737]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="13.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="12.0">12–15</number>
sharply pointed spinose setae ventrally; dorsal ciliation of decumbent short pale setulae, denser distally; without apicoventral extension on T 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BA05F9226112B817" box="[320,330,1785,1809]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
but with strong apical spine. Mid and hind legs slender with fine setae but T 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BFE6F92264F7B817" box="[1187,1199,1785,1809]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="3.0">3</number>
with ‘comb’ of short setae posteroapically. 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8D3A78BADDF8C76181B833" bold="true" box="[408,473,1820,1845]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8D3A78BAABF8C7621FB833" box="[494,583,1820,1845]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[176,1401,193,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1402,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Hemerodromia breviradia sp. nov., holotype ♂. 9. habitus, lateral view; 10. wing; 11. terminalia, lateral view; 12. cercus, dorsal view; 13. subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 14. phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 15. hypandrium, epandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252070/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B96DF8C6621FB833" box="[552,583,1821,1845]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
). Membrane faintly yellow, veins brownish; R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BF37F8F06422B83F" box="[1138,1146,1835,1849]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BFC6F8F064D2B83F" box="[1155,1162,1835,1849]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="3.0">3</number>
short and straight, not strongly curved towards C apically, joining C ~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B986F89F62BEB85A" box="[707,742,1860,1884]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="0.2">0.2</number>
distance between end of R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BF5AF889647FB866" box="[1055,1063,1874,1888]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
and R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BF30F8896425B866" box="[1141,1149,1874,1888]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="4.0">4</number>
; R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BFE5F88964F0B866" box="[1184,1192,1874,1888]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BFF4F88964E0B866" box="[1201,1208,1874,1888]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="5.0">5</number>
fork angle acute (~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BBD2F8B160EFB885" box="[151,183,1898,1923]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="60.0">60</number>
°), distal to position of M 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BA91F8A26181B881" box="[468,473,1913,1927]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BAA6F8A261B4B881" box="[483,492,1913,1927]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="2.0">2</number>
fork by about same length as R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B81DF8A26338B881" box="[856,864,1913,1927]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="4.0">4</number>
; R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B8C6F8A263D3B881" box="[899,907,1913,1927]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B899F8A263BCB881" box="[988,996,1913,1927]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
convergent distally; vein R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BE5BF8A2657EB881" box="[1310,1318,1913,1927]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="5.0">5</number>
~ 2.0X as long as R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BBBAF87B615FB8A8" box="[255,263,1952,1966]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="4.0">4</number>
; cell bm+dm long, ending after at level of R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B9B0F87B62A5B8A8" box="[757,765,1952,1966]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
, ~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B865F84A631AB8AC" box="[800,834,1937,1962]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="2.5">2.5</number>
X as long as cell br. Halter whitish yellow. 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8D3A78BE65F84A65CCB8AC" bold="true" box="[1312,1428,1937,1962]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Tergites 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BBBEF86C617DB8D6" box="[251,293,1975,2000]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="3.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="1.0">1–6</number>
and 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BA27F8636128B8D6" box="[354,368,1976,2000]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="8.0">8</number>
brownish; tergite 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B902F863620DB8C9" box="[583,597,1976,1999]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="7.0">7</number>
and sternites yellowish. Tergites 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B898F863645EB8D6" box="[989,1030,1976,2000]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8</number>
with pale strong setae laterally on posterior margin; tergite 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BAE8F80761E3B8F2" box="[429,443,2012,2036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="8.0">8</number>
slightly shorter than sternite 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B847F807634AB8F2" box="[770,786,2012,2036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="8.0">8</number>
. 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8D3A78B85BF80763F9B8F3" bold="true" box="[798,929,2012,2037]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Terminalia</emphasis>
. Brown. Cercus narrow with pointed apex, distinctly setose on outer face (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8B3A7EB940FF4C6202BFB6" box="[517,602,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[176,1401,193,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1402,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Hemerodromia breviradia sp. nov., holotype ♂. 9. habitus, lateral view; 10. wing; 11. terminalia, lateral view; 12. cercus, dorsal view; 13. subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 14. phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 15. hypandrium, epandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252070/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="214">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8B3A7EB978FF436202BFB6" box="[573,602,152,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="214" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
); right and left cerci close together dorsally (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8B3A7EBF35FF4C649EBFB6" box="[1136,1222,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[176,1401,193,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1402,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Hemerodromia breviradia sp. nov., holotype ♂. 9. habitus, lateral view; 10. wing; 11. terminalia, lateral view; 12. cercus, dorsal view; 13. subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 14. phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 15. hypandrium, epandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252070/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="214">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8B3A7EBFE2FF43649EBFB6" box="[1191,1222,152,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="214" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Epandrium wide basally and gradually tapered towards apex (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8B3A7EB9CBFF6762B8BFD2" box="[654,736,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[176,1401,193,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1402,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Hemerodromia breviradia sp. nov., holotype ♂. 9. habitus, lateral view; 10. wing; 11. terminalia, lateral view; 12. cercus, dorsal view; 13. subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 14. phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 15. hypandrium, epandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252070/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="214">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8B3A7EB986FF6762B8BFD2" box="[707,736,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="214" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
), scattered setae on outer face and spine-like setae apically on inner face (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8B3A7EBA65FF0461F3BFFE" box="[288,427,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[176,1401,193,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1402,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Hemerodromia breviradia sp. nov., holotype ♂. 9. habitus, lateral view; 10. wing; 11. terminalia, lateral view; 12. cercus, dorsal view; 13. subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 14. phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 15. hypandrium, epandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252070/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="214">Figs 11, 13</figureCitation>
). Surstylus absent. Hypandrium rather subtriangular (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8B3A7EBF6DFF0464D8BFFE" box="[1064,1152,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[176,1401,193,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1402,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Hemerodromia breviradia sp. nov., holotype ♂. 9. habitus, lateral view; 10. wing; 11. terminalia, lateral view; 12. cercus, dorsal view; 13. subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 14. phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 15. hypandrium, epandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252070/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="214">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8B3A7EBF27FF0464D8BFFE" box="[1122,1152,223,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="214" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
), without distinct setae; gonocoxal apodemes projecting as narrow process just beyond anterior margin of hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8B3A7EBE46FEDF65D7BE1A" box="[1283,1423,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[176,1401,193,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1402,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Hemerodromia breviradia sp. nov., holotype ♂. 9. habitus, lateral view; 10. wing; 11. terminalia, lateral view; 12. cercus, dorsal view; 13. subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 14. phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 15. hypandrium, epandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252070/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="214">Figs 11, 14</figureCitation>
). Subepandrial sclerite with median triangular anterior projection and median rounded posterior projection (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8B3A7EBE79FEFC65D7BE46" box="[1340,1423,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[176,1401,193,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1402,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Hemerodromia breviradia sp. nov., holotype ♂. 9. habitus, lateral view; 10. wing; 11. terminalia, lateral view; 12. cercus, dorsal view; 13. subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 14. phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 15. hypandrium, epandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252070/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="214">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8B3A7EBE35FEF365D7BE46" box="[1392,1423,296,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="214" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
). Phallus extending just beyond apex of hypandrium, with pointed dorsal projection and median membranous area apically (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8B3A7EBA44FEB4610EBE8E" box="[257,342,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[176,1401,193,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1402,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Hemerodromia breviradia sp. nov., holotype ♂. 9. habitus, lateral view; 10. wing; 11. terminalia, lateral view; 12. cercus, dorsal view; 13. subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 14. phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 15. hypandrium, epandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252070/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="214">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8B3A7EBA72FEAB610EBE8E" box="[311,342,368,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="214" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme lamella flattened in vertical plane, short (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8B3A7EBF79FEB46498BE8E" box="[1084,1216,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[176,1401,193,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1402,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 15. Hemerodromia breviradia sp. nov., holotype ♂. 9. habitus, lateral view; 10. wing; 11. terminalia, lateral view; 12. cercus, dorsal view; 13. subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 14. phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 15. hypandrium, epandrium and phallus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252070/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="214">Figs 11, 14</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8B3A7EBF93FEB46530BE8E" bold="true" box="[1238,1384,367,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="214">Body length</emphasis>
: 2.0 mm; 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8B3A7EBB94FE4F6104BEAB" bold="true" box="[209,348,404,429]" pageId="5" pageNumber="214">wing length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity id="4CC99B3DFF8B3A7EBA2EFE4F619CBEAA" box="[363,452,404,428]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="214" unit="mm" value="1.4">1.4 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8B3A7EBA8AFE4F627EBEAB" bold="true" box="[463,550,404,429]" pageId="5" pageNumber="214">Female</emphasis>
: Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
